author: News Tribune
title: Prep Softball: Gasconade Valley All-Conference Team announced
text:
The Gasconade Valley Conference coaches decided the 2015 all-conference team earlier this week. 
Vienna’s Maddie Stricklanand Jordyn Steffen were named the league’s Co-Most Valuable Player. 
Also earning honors for Vienna were Bailey Wilkinson, Annie John, Megan Wieberg. Kara Harker and Corlis Kloeppel. 
For Belle, Chandler Hicks, Michal Melzar and Brittany White landed on the all-conference team. 
Cuba’s Taylor Williams, Kristyn England, Hannah Mitchell, Mykayla Forester and Tiffany Gruver made the team. 
Steelville’s Reece Weber, Mykenzie Livesay and Kaytalin Rivera also made the cut. 
Callie Shelton was the lone Bourbon player to make the team. ﻿
